World Sugar Balance to Move Into Surplus, According to Sucden

-- B y   I s i s   A l m e i d a
-- 
2011-05-04T15:01:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-04/world-sugar-balance-to-move-into-surplus-according-to-sucden.html
Following are remarks on the world
sugar balance from Pierre-Henri Dietz, an analyst at Sucden, the
trading arm of Sucres et Denrees SA. He commented by e-mail
today.  “We are moving from a tight situation into a surplus from
July onwards.”  “The surplus will be there up to the end of 2011.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
